body:
As someone in tech, I can tell you right now that 10 hours of downtime for a technical issue is indicative that some major damage control is going on behind the scenes. It does not take 10 hours to bring backups on line, or to roll back a to a previous branch. There are no backbone issue with network infrastructure (that I'm aware of) today, and the issue is geographically widespread suggesting issues at the source.

&amp;#x200B;

Would not be surprised to see a PII data breach with possibly lost data at this point. No way in hell 10 hours is the resolution for something as commonplace as the aforementioned.

&amp;#x200B;

Something big went down and RH is ass covering while hiding it. Move your money.
